tasks.description:
Create a concise cheat-sheet comment block (or internal note) capturing the 6-step mechanical pattern to apply to every model method. This is for developer reference during implementation:

```
// PATTERN: Adding tx to a model method
// Step 1: Add tx?: DrizzleClient as last parameter
// Step 2: Replace getDb() → this.getClient(tx)
// Step 3: findWithRelations: relations type = Record<string, boolean | Record<string, unknown>>
// Step 4a: this.findAll(where, opts, conds, tx)  — tx is 4th positional
// Step 4b: this.count(where, { tx })             — tx in options object
// Step 4c: this.findOne(where, tx)               — tx positional (confirm from BaseModel)
// Step 5: Remove getDb import from file header
// Step 6: Add import type { DrizzleClient } from '@repo/db'
```

Also document the fallback pattern for findWithRelations:
```ts
override async findWithRelations(
  where: WhereClause,
  relations: Record<string, boolean | Record<string, unknown>>,
  tx?: DrizzleClient
): Promise<Entity | null> {
  // ...
  return this.findOne(where, tx); // MUST pass tx
}
```

No files modified. Reference file: internal developer note only.

Test requirements: None — documentation task.

Apply tx threading to ExchangeRateModel. This model uses a subquery pattern — careful attention required.

File: `packages/db/src/models/exchange-rate/exchange-rate.model.ts`

Methods to fix:
1. `findLatestRate(fromCurrency, toCurrency, tx?)` — replace getDb() with this.getClient(tx); contains subquery using db reference
2. `findLatestRates(currency, tx?)` — replace getDb() with this.getClient(tx)
3. `findRateHistory(from, to, options, tx?)` — replace getDb() with this.getClient(tx)
4. `findManualOverrides(tx?)` — replace getDb() with this.getClient(tx)
5. `findAllWithDateRange(from, to, tx?)` — SUBQUERY PATTERN: the inner subquery reference must also use this.getClient(tx), NOT a separate getDb() call

Critical subquery pattern:
```ts
// BEFORE:
const db = getDb();
const sub = db.select()...;
const result = db.select()...from(sub)...;
// AFTER:
const db = this.getClient(tx);
const sub = db.select()...;  // same db reference
const result = db.select()...from(sub)...;
```

Test requirements:
- File: `packages/db/src/models/exchange-rate/__tests__/exchange-rate.model.test.ts`
- Test each method with tx threading
- Special test for findAllWithDateRange: verify both outer and inner queries use same client reference
